On Wed, 25 Jan 2006, George Lyle wrote:

> > I don't have any experience with using O2 sensors on T1 engine, so I don't know where's a good place to mount it...anyone?
> 
 Well, it can't be closer than two feet to the exhaust port and also can't
 be close to the tip of the exhaust.  I'd say that the best place for the
 sensor is right in the middle of the muffler, but it might be a bear to
 weld a proper bung to the thin sheet metal.
